assessment_comment: Damaged near outlet. Small stream but flowing. Middle of pipe filled with fines.

Channel with and gradient estimated. Culvert is fully backwatered due to beaver dams at this time and passable but might be a good idea to assess flow velocities in the spring at higher flows.  Habitat confirmation could be conducted to get an idea of fish values and habitat values to inform if  are an issue.
Covert has baffles in it but has significant riprap at outlet that creates cascade approximately 1.5 m high.
This is a rough ATV Road to this point and appears to be the end of the accessible remnants of this road.
